# Song Duration Configuration
# Format: One line per track
# Format: track_number,duration_seconds
#
# Copy this file to your SD card as "songconfig.txt" (without .example extension)
# Then edit it with actual durations of your MP3 files
#
# To find MP3 duration:
# - Right-click MP3 → Properties → Details (shows bit rate)
# - For 128 kbps: duration ≈ file_size_MB × 60 seconds
# - Or use ffprobe: ffprobe -v error -select_streams a:0 -show_entries stream=duration your_song.mp3
# - Or use online tools: mediainfo.online
#
# Example for 128kbps MP3s:
# - 240 seconds ≈ 3.6 MB file
# - 180 seconds ≈ 2.7 MB file
# - 300 seconds ≈ 4.5 MB file

1,240
2,186
3,320
4,255
5,195
